#! clause: L6.4
#! clause: L7.6
#! mode: static
#! stage: parse
# In a construct header a `do … end` opens the construct body, not a block
# argument to a call in the header (S-4). To pass a block to a call in a header,
# parenthesize it: the inner `do … end` is `stream()`'s block argument, the
# outer `do … end` is the `while` body.
while (stream() do (line) handle(line) end) do
    step()
end
